# Technical Details

This section is best placed **after "Working Principle"** and **before "Telegram Bot Configuration"** in your README. It explains the system architecture, communication flow, networking, protocols, and security without overwhelming the reader.

---

## Frontend (User Interface)

The frontend consists of the components that the user directly interacts with.

* Telegram mobile or desktop application
* 16×2 I2C LCD for message display
* YES (OK) response button
* NO (BUSY) response button
* Passive buzzer for audio notifications
* Internet status LED
* ESP32 as the main control interface

---

## Backend (Processing System)

The backend is responsible for processing all communication and device operations.

* ESP32 Microcontroller
* Telegram Bot API
* Telegram Cloud Servers
* Wi-Fi Router / Internet Gateway
* NTP Time Server for timestamp synchronization
* Internal message logging system
* Message processing and response handling firmware

---

## Communication Architecture

The complete communication path is:

```
Telegram User
      │
      ▼
Telegram Cloud Server
      │
      ▼
Telegram Bot API
      │
 HTTPS (TLS Encrypted)
      │
      ▼
Wi-Fi Router
      │
      ▼
ESP32 Microcontroller
      │
 ┌────┼────┐
 ▼    ▼    ▼
LCD  Buzzer Buttons
```

---

## Networking Specifications

* Wireless Standard: IEEE 802.11 b/g/n (Wi-Fi)
* Network Type: Infrastructure Mode
* Internet Connectivity: Wi-Fi Router
* Communication Method: Client–Server Architecture
* Message Retrieval: Telegram Bot API Polling
* Time Synchronization: Network Time Protocol (NTP)
* Internet Verification: DNS Connectivity Check
* Network Addressing: Dynamic IP (DHCP)

